main event: Technicians of the air control department of the Venezuelan armed forces reported a formation of flying objects in the Caracas skies, which were described as absolutely unusual and disappeared in the direction of El Valle.
interesting points: The flying objects were described as absolutely unusual by the technicians.
The objects disappeared in the direction of El Valle, indicating a clear direction of movement.
The report suggests a lack of maneuverability and speculates that the objects were probably meteors based on their formation.
The sighting took place in Caracas, Venezuela, in May 1958.
The report is from Project Blue Book, a U.S. Air Force program that investigated UFOs.
witnesses: technicians of the Venezuelan air force
